overview.longBusinessSummary: Virtu Financial, Inc. operates as a financial services company in the United States, Ireland, and internationally. It operates through two segments: Market Making and Execution Services. The company's product includes offerings in execution, liquidity sourcing, analytics and broker-neutral, capital markets, and multi-dealer platforms in workflow technology. Its product allows its clients to trade on various venues across 50 countries and in various asset classes, including global equities, ETFs, options, foreign exchange, futures, fixed income, cryptocurrencies, and myriad other commodities. The company's multi-asset analytics platform provides a range of pre- and post-trade services, data products, and compliance tools for clients to invest, trade, and manage risk across global markets. Virtu Financial, Inc. was founded in 2008 and is headquartered in New York, New York.
